OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F379A1778238120
OL,3,CPub punch killer convicted after
OL,4,Cgrandfather's death
OL,6,FA 36-year-old has been found guilty of
OL,7,Fmanslaughter after he punched a
OL,8,Fgrandfather who was helping him
OL,9,Foutside a pub in Leicestershire.
OL,11,FDavid Darke died in hospital six days
OL,12,Fafter sustaining a head injury outside
OL,13,Fthe Crown Inn in Appleby Magna on 21
OL,14,FDecember last year.
OL,16,FNathan Gothard, 36, of Church Street
OL,17,Fwas today found guilty of manslaughter
OL,18,Fand not guilty of murder at Leicester
OL,19,FCrown Court.
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G1/12
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,380,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37902
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F379A1778238120
OL,3,CPub punch killer convicted after
OL,4,Cgrandfather's death
OL,6,FAn inquest into his death in February
OL,7,Ffound that Darke's cause of death were
OL,8,Fserious head injuries after being
OL,9,Fpunched and falling backwards onto the
OL,10,Ffloor.
OL,12,FHe stood in the dock with his head
OL,13,Fbowed after the guilty verdict was
OL,14,Freturned, while members of Mr Darke's
OL,15,Ffamily sitting in the public gallery
OL,16,Fsaid "yes" before wiping their tears.
OL,26,@xD@FOUxD@JO]
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G2/12
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,380,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37903
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F379A1778238120
OL,3,CPub punch killer convicted after
OL,4,Cgrandfather's death
OL,6,FProsecutor, Peter Joyce KC, told the
OL,7,Fjury of seven men and five women that
OL,8,Fthe atmosphere in the Crown Inn on the
OL,9,Fevening of December 21 last year was
OL,10,F"menacing, threatening, argumentative
OL,11,Fand disputing" because of Gothard's
OL,12,Fbehaviour.
OL,14,FMr Joyce KC said Darke was hit so hard
OL,15,Fthat it killed him and that it was not
OL,16,Fan act of self-defence by Gothard.
OL,26,@rD@AOUsD@NO]
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G3/12
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,380,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37904
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F379A1778238120
OL,3,CPub punch killer convicted after
OL,4,Cgrandfather's death
OL,6,FThe jury heard that Gothard first
OL,7,Farrived at the pub at around 4pm and
OL,8,Fat 7pm, a group of about 10 people who
OL,9,Fwere part of a Christmas party arrived
OL,10,Fat the pub from the Best Western hotel
OL,11,Fon the other side of the village.
OL,13,FThe court heard that Mr Gothard began
OL,14,Fbehaving inappropriately with female
OL,15,Fmembers of the group and making
OL,16,F'remarks' to them.
OL,18,FJurors are told that Mr Gothard said
OL,19,Fthe pub was "his terrain" and they
OL,20,Fwere in his pub.
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G4/12
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,380,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37905
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F379A1778238120
OL,3,CPub punch killer convicted after
OL,4,Cgrandfather's death
OL,6,FThe prosecutor said: "The defendant,
OL,7,FNathan Gothard, was already in the pub
OL,8,Fhaving arrived just before 4pm.
OL,10,F"During the course of the evening,
OL,11,FNathan Gothard began to behave
OL,12,Finappropriately, making unwelcome
OL,13,Fadvances and remarks to female members
OL,14,Fof the group who had come from the
OL,15,Fstaff party and making clear to them
OL,16,Fit was his terrain - they were in his
OL,17,Fpub."
OL,26,@nD@VOUrD@AOUyD@EO]
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G5/12
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,380,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37906
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F379A1778238120
OL,3,CPub punch killer convicted after
OL,4,Cgrandfather's death
OL,6,FThe judge also said after 9pm he
OL,7,Fbecame menacing and argumentative and
OL,8,Fthe landlady and her partner
OL,9,Fintervened to calm things down.
OL,11,FThey then succeeded in escorting him
OL,12,Fout of the back door and tried to
OL,13,Fencourage him to go home as he lived
OL,14,Fvery close to the pub.
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G6/12
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,380,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37907
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F379A1778238120
OL,3,CPub punch killer convicted after
OL,4,Cgrandfather's death
OL,6,FMr Joyce continued: "Instead of going
OL,7,Fhome, the defendant Mr Gothard went
OL,8,Fall the way up the outside of the pub
OL,9,Fto continue his fights or disputes or
OL,10,Farguments with those who had been at
OL,11,Fthe party, who he knew and saw were
OL,12,Fcoming out of the front door of the
OL,13,Fpub.
OL,15,F"In simple terms, he went to look for
OL,16,Fthem."
OL,18,FThe jury was then told that Darke
OL,19,Fapproached Gothard to help him.
OL,26,@nD@UOUwD@AOUxD@FO]
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G7/12
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,380,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37908
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F379A1778238120
OL,3,CPub punch killer convicted after
OL,4,Cgrandfather's death
OL,6,FMr Joyce said: "David Darke, the man
OL,7,Fsoon to be killed, in fact picked him
OL,8,Fup and helped pull him to his feet.
OL,10,F"The defendant, in his rage, after
OL,11,Flosing the fight he had picked,
OL,12,Fattacked Mr Darke to save his own face.
OL,14,F"He hit him so hard that he killed
OL,15,Fhim. You do that in your rage because
OL,16,Fof intent to cause someone really
OL,17,Fserious harm ` that's murder.
OL,26,@nD@POUrD@AOUvD@AOU
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G8/12
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,380,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37909
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F379A1778238120
OL,3,CPub punch killer convicted after
OL,4,Cgrandfather's death
OL,6,FThe prosecutor said that after the
OL,7,Fattack, Gothard told police that an
OL,8,F"elderly male kept saying he was going
OL,9,Fto kill me and bury me".
OL,11,FGothard claimed he was acting in self-
OL,12,Fdefence after Mr Darke grabbed him and
OL,13,Fthreatened to kill him.
OL,15,FHe told the court he felt "ridiculed"
OL,16,Fby a group of people inside the bar on
OL,17,Fthe evening of December 21.
OL,26,@pD@AOUqD@WO]wD@[OUwD@eO]
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G9/12
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,380,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37910
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F379A1778238120
OL,3,CPub punch killer convicted after
OL,4,Cgrandfather's death
OL,6,FGothard's defence barrister said in a
OL,7,Fclosing statement to the jury: "Oaf,
OL,8,Faggressor, murderer ` that's what the
OL,9,Fprosecution say Nathan Gothard is.
OL,11,F"Nathan Gothard did not know David
OL,12,FDarke, had no beef, no bad blood with
OL,13,FDavid Darke. Had no reason, you may
OL,14,Fthink, to want him harmed, to want him
OL,15,Fdead.
OL,17,F"We have threats made by David Darke
OL,18,F'I'm going to bury you'. Those threats
OL,19,Fare confirmed by witnesses.
OL,26,@oD@`OUsD@AOUyD@AOU
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4         G10/12
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,380,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37911
SC,0011
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F379A1778238120
OL,3,CPub punch killer convicted after
OL,4,Cgrandfather's death
OL,6,F"Not a single threat was made by
OL,7,FNathan Gothard."
OL,9,FMr Bhatia added: "Who was the
OL,10,Faggressor inside the pub? We submit,
OL,11,Fon the evidence, it was not him. He
OL,12,Fmay have been acting like a prat, he
OL,13,Fmay have been acting like an oaf, but
OL,14,Fhe was not the aggressor."
OL,16,FBut prosecutors accused Gothard of
OL,17,Fcreating a "menacing, threatening,
OL,18,Fargumentative and disputing"
OL,19,Fatmosphere.
OL,26,@nD@AOUoD@PO]qD@ROUvD@ZO]yD@LOUzD@\O]
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4         G11/12
